@page
@model StudioBriefcase.Pages.Tutorials.Vulkan._vulkanSDKModel
@{
    Layout = null;
}

<div class="container-fluid size_container mt-3 mb-2">
    <div class="text-center">
        <h2>Installing Vulkan SDK</h2>
    </div>

    <div>
        <h6>Environment</h6>
        <ul>
            <li>Visual Studio 2022</li>
            <li>RenderDoc</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-3">
        <h6>Download Links</h6>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="https://www.lunarg.com/vulkan-sdk/"> Vulkan SDK from LunarG</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://renderdoc.org/"> Renderdoc Graphics API Troubleshooting</a></li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div>
        <p>LunarG created and maintains the Vulkan Software Development Kit. The software Development kit comes with a collection of essential tools to assist
            developers.
        </p>
        <h6>Tools and headers that come with the Software Development Kit</h6>
        <ul>
            <li>GLM headers - OpenGL Math Library</li>
            <li>shaderc headers - Runtime Compiling of Shading Languages to SPIR-V Binary</li>
            <li>glslangValidator application - Manual Conversion of GLSL to SPIR-V Binary</li>
            <li>glslc application - Google's Manual Conversion of GLSL to SPIR-V Binary</li>
        </ul>
    </div>


    <div>
        <h6>LunarG SDK Introduction</h6>
        <p>The LunarG has robust easy to use documentation. The Getting Started section has a detailed introduction the kits contents.</p>
    </div>

        <div class="accordion">

            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h5 class="accordion-header">
                    <button class="button_accordian collapsed FG" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#installing" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="installing">
                        <span>Installing SDK</span>
                        <ion-icon class="expanded" name="chevron-forward-outline"></ion-icon>
                    </button>
                </h5>
                <div class="accoridion-collapse collapse" id="installing">
                    <div class="accordion-body BG">
                        <p>Installation is straight forward. The only question have are what extra tools you will need
                        when the installer asks. See the following image.
                        <img src="~/images/Vulkan/SDKInstall/VulkanSetup.png" class="fit_image" />
                    </p>
                    
                    <p>This tutorial will use the glm headers, and if you didn't add them during the setup, run the maintenancetool
                        application and you can check the box and add them post installation.
                    <img src="~/images/Vulkan/SDKInstall/VulkanMaintenanceTool_Pic.png" class="fit_image" />
                    </p>
                    <p>"C:\VulkanSDK\1.3.250.0\maintenancetool.exe"</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h5 class="accordion-header">
                    <button class="button_accordian collapsed FG" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#VSTemplates" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="VSTemplates">
                        <span>Add Visual Studio Template Projects</span>
                        <ion-icon class="expanded" name="chevron-forward-outline"></ion-icon>
                    </button>
                </h5>
                <div class="accoridion-collapse collapse" id="VSTemplates">
                    <div class="accordion-body BG">
                        <p>
                            The VulkanSDK comes with templates for Visual Studio. Do not extract these, Copy and paste them directly
                        into the respective Visual Studio Template path. Visual Studio is able to handle zipped files.
                        <img src="~/images/Vulkan/SDKInstall//SDK_VSTemplates.png" class="fit_image" />
                        </p>
                        <span> C:\Users\username\Documents\Visual Studio YYYY\Templates\ProjectTemplates\Visual C++ Project</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>


        </div>


    </div>
